  "abstract": "Field propagation in a cylindrical, transversely balanced corrugated waveguide which is filled with chiral medium is considered. The eigenfields inside this kind of waveguide are circularly polarized. In this study, the spherically symmetric modes are considered. For small chirality parameter values, there exists weak coupling between the eigenfields, which results in a change in polarization of the propagating field. This effect makes it possible to produce mode transformers and phase shifters for circular waveguides. © 2000 John Wiley & Sons, Inc. Microwave Opt Technol Lett 27: 168–171, 2000.",
